<h2 id="rewardpot" data-title="How your Reward Pot works">Reward Pot</h2>

<p>Our concept is built on small scale mutualisation of risk between you and your friends and contacts (“Connections”) (and collectively “Group”). You will not be paid introductory fees. But if the performance of your Group produces good results
    together, then we will “reward” you by making premium rebates to you as set put below.</p>

<p>Your Group can be as small or large as you want but your Reward Pot is limited to 80% of the premium shown on your policy schedule (the Reward Pot Limit). For each member of your Group who joins within 60 days of the start date of your policy, £10
    is put into your Reward Pot, up to the Reward Pot Limit but this is reduced to £2 if one of your Group members makes a claim within your first 60 days of your policy start. For each member of your Group that joins after 60 days from the start of your
    policy], £2 is put into your Reward Pot, up to the Reward Pot Limit. Each of your Group members also has a Reward Pot associated to their Connections, which operates in the same way as yours (so money will also be added to their Reward Pot when you
    connect to them).
</p>

<p>Example of your Reward Pot value, if your insurance premium is £{{ maxPotValue }}
    and your group members join in the first 60 days:</p>

<table>
    <tr>
        <th>Number of connections</th>
        <th>Reward Pot Value</th>
        <th>% of Insurance cost</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>0</td>
        <td>£0</td>
        <td>0%</td>
    </tr>
    {% for i in 1..maxConnections - 1 %}
        <tr>
            <td>{{ i }}</td>
            <td>£{{ i * 10 }}</td>
            <td>{{ (100 * i * 10 / yearlyPremium) |number_format(0, '.', ',') }}%</td>
        </tr>
    {% endfor %}
    <tr>
        <td>{{ maxConnections }}</td>
